TEST CASES USING BROWSER DEVTOOLS
TC-DT01 – Validate Responsiveness Across Multiple Devices

Objective: Verify layout behavior using DevTools Device Emulation
Steps:

Open website.

Press F12 to open DevTools.

Select “Toggle Device Toolbar”.

Test layouts using devices: iPhone 12, Pixel 7, Samsung Galaxy S8, iPad, Moto G4.

Inspect header, buttons, text alignment and forms.
Expected Result:
All layouts adjust correctly without breaking or overlapping elements.
Actual Result:
(Your result here)

TC-DT02 – Detect Layout Breaks With Custom Widths

Objective: Identify breakpoints that are not defined in CSS
Steps:

Open DevTools → “Toggle Device Toolbar”.

Manually drag the screen width to arbitrary values (340px → 600px).

Verify alignment, images and buttons at each width.
Expected Result:
No layout break occurs at any width.
Actual Result:
(Your result here)

TC-DT03 – Validate Network Requests (Status Codes & Timing)

Objective: Ensure all network requests load successfully
Steps:

Open DevTools → Network.

Reload the page.

Check each request: status code, size, timing.

Identify any failed, delayed or blocked resources.
Expected Result:
All requests return 200/304; no failed (404/500) or slow (>2s) resources.
Actual Result:
(Your result here)

TC-DT04 – Validate Console Errors

Objective: Ensure the website loads without JavaScript errors
Steps:

Open DevTools → Console tab.

Reload the page.

Check for errors or warnings.
Expected Result:
No JavaScript errors, no red error messages. Acceptable number of warnings allowed.
Actual Result:
(Your result here)

TC-DT05 – Performance Audit Using Lighthouse

Objective: Measure page performance, accessibility and SEO
Steps:

Open DevTools → Lighthouse.

Select “Mobile” mode.

Run the audit.

Record Performance, Accessibility, SEO and Best Practices scores.
Expected Result:
Performance ≥ 70
Accessibility ≥ 80
No critical issues found.
Actual Result:
(Your result here)

TC-DT06 – Simulate Slow Network (Throttling)

Objective: Validate behavior under poor connectivity
Steps:

Open DevTools → Network.

Select “Fast 3G” then “Slow 3G”.

Reload the page.

Observe loading times and element appearance.
Expected Result:
Content loads progressively, essential elements load within 5–10s, no complete failure.
Actual Result:
(Your result here)

TC-DT07 – Check Local Storage Usage

Objective: Verify that the website properly stores and retrieves data
Steps:

Open DevTools → Application → Local Storage.

Navigate through the website.

Observe which keys are created or updated.

Refresh the page and ensure values persist.
Expected Result:
Stored values are correct and persist across sessions when expected.
Actual Result:
(Your result here)

TC-DT08 – Validate Session Storage Behavior

Objective: Confirm temporary values are stored only for the active session
Steps:

Open DevTools → Application → Session Storage.

Trigger actions (form inputs, navigation).

Close the tab and reopen the site.
Expected Result:
Session storage clears when tab is closed.
Actual Result:
(Your result here)

TC-DT09 – Check Cookies (Security Flags)

Objective: Ensure cookies comply with security standards
Steps:

Open DevTools → Application → Cookies.

Validate attributes: Secure, HttpOnly, SameSite.
Expected Result:
Cookies must not expose sensitive data; secure flags applied when appropriate.
Actual Result:
(Your result here)

TC-DT10 – Observe Render Performance (FPS Meter)

Objective: Detect UI lag or animation issues
Steps:

Open DevTools → Rendering.

Enable FPS Meter.

Interact with animations, scroll page.
Expected Result:
FPS remains stable (>40), no visible lag.
Actual Result:
(Your result here)

TC-DT11 – Validate Media Queries

Objective: Ensure CSS media queries trigger correctly
Steps:

Inspect elements → Styles.

Adjust widths in Device Toolbar.

Verify which media queries activate.
Expected Result:
Correct CSS rules apply at each breakpoint.
Actual Result:
(Your result here)

TC-DT12 – Test Dark/Light Mode (If Exists)

Objective: Validate theme switching using prefers-color-scheme
Steps:

Open DevTools → Rendering.

Force dark mode.

Force light mode.
Expected Result:
Colours, shadows and icons adapt properly for each theme.
Actual Result:
(Your result here)

TC-DT13 – Validate Lazy Loading of Images

Objective: Ensure images load only when visible
Steps:

Open DevTools → Network.

Scroll through the page slowly.

Check image loading behavior (look for “lazy” flag).
Expected Result:
Images load only when approaching viewport.
Actual Result:
(Your result here)

TC-DT14 – Detect Layout Shift (CLS Test)

Objective: Identify elements moving during load
Steps:

Open DevTools → Performance.

Record page load.

Observe Cumulative Layout Shift score.
Expected Result:
CLS should be low (<0.1). No major shifting of text/buttons.
Actual Result:
(Your result here)

